3. Index Skill Execution (Index Requests Use This Directly)
==============================================================================

Skill: index-enterprise-documents
Location: .claude/skills/index-enterprise-documents/SKILL.md

Command (from SKILL.md Commands section):
  CHROMA_PATH=.cache/task2-skill-chroma \
  uv run python .claude/skills/index-enterprise-documents/scripts/ingest.py \
    --data-dir tests/fixtures/task2-input \
    --reset \
    --no-vision

Output summary:
  {'processed_files': 2, 'failed_files': 0, 'chunk_count': 10, 'skipped': False}

Processing details:
  ✓ tests/fixtures/task2-input/sample_enterprise_report.pdf: 4 records → 5 chunks
  ✓ tests/fixtures/task2-input/sample_product_strategy.pptx: 5 records → 5 chunks

Execution confirms:
  - End-to-end workflow (parse → chunk → embed → persist)
  - Index requests do not need a separate parse Skill invocation
  - Write isolation (only writes to CHROMA_PATH)
  - No source file modification
  - Vision disabled with --no-vision flag
  - Temporary index at .cache/task2-skill-chroma (not default chroma/)

