5. Official Pattern Compliance
==============================================================================

Based on https://code.claude.com/docs/en/skills and
https://kaochenlong.com/claude-code-skills:

✓ File structure:
  skill-name/
  ├── SKILL.md           # Instructions with frontmatter
  └── scripts/           # Executable code
      └── script.py

✓ Frontmatter fields:
  - name: skill-name (lowercase, hyphens)
  - description: what and when to use (>80 chars)
  - allowed-tools: Bash(uv run python *) for pre-authorization and dependencies

✓ SKILL.md content:
  - Clear sections: Inputs, Outputs, Safe Execution Boundary, Commands
  - ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR} for script references
  - Executable command examples with uv run python
  - Usage notes and guidance

✓ Invocation model:
  - Claude reads SKILL.md when relevant
  - Claude executes commands via Bash tool
  - Scripts located relative to skill directory
  - No wrapper scripts required

